(Microtransfer Printing: Principles, Process Variants, Applications, and Challenges) Tj
0 -15 Td
() Tj
0 -15 Td
(Abstract) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Microtransfer printing \(MTP\) is a deterministic assembly method that retrieves microscale or) Tj
0 -15 Td
(nanoscale material inks from a donor substrate and places them onto a target substrate with) Tj
0 -15 Td
(high spatial control. It is an important route for heterogeneous integration because it allows) Tj
0 -15 Td
(separately optimized materials and devices to be assembled onto flexible, stretchable, curved,) Tj
0 -15 Td
(or photonic target platforms.) Tj
0 -15 Td
() Tj
0 -15 Td
(1. Introduction) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Microtransfer printing emerged as a manufacturing strategy for heterogeneous integration when) Tj
0 -15 Td
(monolithic fabrication or wafer bonding became too restrictive for systems that combine) Tj
0 -15 Td
(dissimilar materials, processing temperatures, or substrate formats. Meitl et al. established) Tj
0 -15 Td
(the key idea of kinetic control of adhesion between an elastomeric stamp and a microstructured) Tj
0 -15 Td
(ink, enabling deterministic pick-up and release without dedicated adhesive layers [1]. Park et) Tj
0 -15 Td
(al. extended the method to functional inorganic LEDs on deformable and semitransparent display) Tj
0 -15 Td
(platforms [2]. Carlson et al. later framed transfer printing as a broad family of assembly) Tj
0 -15 Td
(techniques for micro- and nanomaterials in electronics, optoelectronics, and bio-integrated) Tj
0 -15 Td
(systems [3].) Tj
0 -15 Td
() Tj
0 -15 Td
(2. Operating Principle) Tj
0 -15 Td
(The basic workflow contains fabrication of transferable inks on a donor wafer, retrieval by a) Tj
0 -15 Td
(stamp or transfer head, alignment to the receiver substrate, and controlled release onto the) Tj
0 -15 Td
(final target. In elastomeric stamp printing, rapid peeling raises interfacial adhesion enough) Tj
0 -15 Td
(for pick-up, while slow peeling or altered contact conditions favor release to the receiver) Tj
0 -15 Td
([1]. Interfacial fracture mechanics strongly affects the outcome. Kim-Lee et al. showed that) Tj
0 -15 Td
(preferred crack paths depend on interface toughness, stamp geometry, flaw size, and membrane) Tj
0 -15 Td
(thickness [5]. Review papers further emphasize the roles of seal material, modulus, surface) Tj
0 -15 Td
(microstructure, preload, peel rate, and thermal state [6,8].) Tj
0 -15 Td
() Tj
0 -15 Td
(3. Major Process Variants) Tj
0 -15 Td
(The most established variant is elastomeric transfer printing, typically using PDMS or related) Tj
0 -15 Td
(soft stamps. Its strengths are conformal contact, material versatility, and compatibility with) Tj
0 -15 Td
(fragile thin-film devices; its weaknesses include stamp wear, process sensitivity, and scaling) Tj
0 -15 Td
(difficulty for massive arrays [3,6]. Laser-driven micro-transfer printing reduces dependence on) Tj
0 -15 Td
(receiver-surface preparation by using laser-induced delamination for non-contact release [4].) Tj
0 -15 Td
(More recently, Park et al. reported a micro-vacuum-assisted selective transfer method with) Tj
0 -15 Td
(independently controlled suction channels and a reported transfer yield of 98.06 percent for) Tj
0 -15 Td
(selective heterogeneous assembly [10].) Tj
0 -15 Td
() Tj
0 -15 Td
(4. Representative Applications) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Flexible and stretchable inorganic electronics are the best known application area because) Tj
0 -15 Td
(transfer printing decouples device growth from final assembly on soft substrates [6]. Displays) Tj
0 -15 Td
(are a classic demonstration: Park et al. showed printed assemblies of microscale inorganic LEDs) Tj
0 -15 Td
(for deformable and semitransparent systems [2]. Silicon photonics is another strong application) Tj
0 -15 Td
(area because active III-V devices and other optimized photonic building blocks can be placed) Tj
