(5. Current Bottlenecks) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Industrial deployment still depends on solving several bottlenecks. Throughput and defectivity) Tj
0 -15 Td
(remain tightly coupled, so the field needs massively parallel transfer with repair strategies) Tj
0 -15 Td
(and near-zero missing-chip rates. Mechanics-driven variability remains important because small) Tj
0 -15 Td
(changes in interface energy, stamp aging, or device geometry can alter release behavior [5].) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Heterogeneous integration workflows must also connect transfer printing to upstream device) Tj
0 -15 Td
(singulation and downstream electrical, optical, or thermal interconnection at acceptable cost) Tj
0 -15 Td
([3,6,8].) Tj
0 -15 Td
() Tj
0 -15 Td
(6. Conclusion) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Microtransfer printing has evolved from an adhesion-switching concept into a serious) Tj
0 -15 Td
(heterogeneous integration platform. Early work established deterministic pick-and-place) Tj
0 -15 Td
(mechanics, later work broadened demonstrations and modeling, and recent studies have focused on) Tj
0 -15 Td
(scalable, selective, and lower-damage architectures. Its long-term importance is highest where) Tj
0 -15 Td
(monolithic integration is impossible or economically unattractive, especially in flexible) Tj
0 -15 Td
(electronics, micro-LED displays, and heterogeneous photonic integrated circuits.) Tj
0 -15 Td
